======================================================================
PART 2: LUCAS / FIBONACCI CONNECTION
======================================================================

Key relations (x = 2):
  I(P_k, x) satisfies: f(k) = f(k-1) + x·f(k-2), f(0)=1, f(1)=1+x
  At x=2: f(k) = f(k-1) + 2·f(k-2), f(0)=1, f(1)=3
  Char eq: t² = t + 2 → t = 2, -1
  Solution: f(k) = (2^{k+2} - (-1)^k) / 3 (Jacobsthal-related!)

  I(C_k, x) = I(P_k, x) - x·I(P_{k-2}, x) [standard identity]
  Wait, let's verify:

  k=3: I(C_k)=7, I(P_k)=11, I(P_k)-I(C_k)=4, 2*I(P_1)=6
  k=4: I(C_k)=17, I(P_k)=21, I(P_k)-I(C_k)=4, 2*I(P_2)=10
  k=5: I(C_k)=31, I(P_k)=43, I(P_k)-I(C_k)=12, 2*I(P_3)=22
  k=6: I(C_k)=65, I(P_k)=85, I(P_k)-I(C_k)=20, 2*I(P_4)=42
  k=7: I(C_k)=127, I(P_k)=171, I(P_k)-I(C_k)=44, 2*I(P_5)=86
  k=8: I(C_k)=257, I(P_k)=341, I(P_k)-I(C_k)=84, 2*I(P_6)=170
  k=9: I(C_k)=511, I(P_k)=683, I(P_k)-I(C_k)=172, 2*I(P_7)=342

  k=3: I(C_k)=7, I(P_2)+2·I(P_0)=7, match=True
  k=4: I(C_k)=17, I(P_3)+2·I(P_1)=17, match=True
  k=5: I(C_k)=31, I(P_4)+2·I(P_2)=31, match=True
  k=6: I(C_k)=65, I(P_5)+2·I(P_3)=65, match=True
  k=7: I(C_k)=127, I(P_6)+2·I(P_4)=127, match=True
  k=8: I(C_k)=257, I(P_7)+2·I(P_5)=257, match=True
  k=9: I(C_k)=511, I(P_8)+2·I(P_6)=511, match=True

======================================================================
PART 3: JACOBSTHAL NUMBERS AND H SPECTRUM
======================================================================
Jacobsthal: J(n) = (2^n - (-1)^n)/3
Path:  I(P_k, 2) = (2^{k+2} - (-1)^k)/3 = 4·J(k) + (-1)^k·(4-1)/3

  k= 0: J(k)=    0, I(P_k,2)=    1, I(C_k,2)=  N/A
  k= 1: J(k)=    1, I(P_k,2)=    3, I(C_k,2)=  N/A
  k= 2: J(k)=    1, I(P_k,2)=    5, I(C_k,2)=  N/A
  k= 3: J(k)=    3, I(P_k,2)=   11, I(C_k,2)=    7
  k= 4: J(k)=    5, I(P_k,2)=   21, I(C_k,2)=   17
  k= 5: J(k)=   11, I(P_k,2)=   43, I(C_k,2)=   31
  k= 6: J(k)=   21, I(P_k,2)=   85, I(C_k,2)=   65
  k= 7: J(k)=   43, I(P_k,2)=  171, I(C_k,2)=  127
  k= 8: J(k)=   85, I(P_k,2)=  341, I(C_k,2)=  257
  k= 9: J(k)=  171, I(P_k,2)=  683, I(C_k,2)=  511
  k=10: J(k)=  341, I(P_k,2)= 1365, I(C_k,2)= 1025
  k=11: J(k)=  683, I(P_k,2)= 2731, I(C_k,2)= 2047

--- IDENTIFICATION ---
I(C_k, 2) = L_k where L_k = 2^k + (-1)^k
  = Lucas numbers for char eq t² - t - 2 = 0 (roots 2, -1)
I(P_k, 2) = U_k where U_k = (2^{k+1} - (-1)^{k+1})/3
  = Chebyshev-like second kind for same characteristic

Both satisfy SAME recurrence: a(k) = a(k-1) + 2·a(k-2)
Cycle initial: a(1)=1(?), a(2)=... hmm, let's just use closed form

